# (explicit pointer-of-aliased-variable; opt-in via
# `aliased` qualifier), R272 C POSIX getopt (no
# binding — caller switch-cases on getopt's return
# value), R302 Clojure babashka.cli (parsed map),
# R303 Gleam Glint (closure-bound).  CLI11's
# approach: COMPILE-TIME-TYPED REFERENCE BINDING
# — closest analog: Boost.Program_Options
# `po::value<T>(&target)` but CLI11 deduces type
# whereas Boost requires explicit `<T>` template.
# Corpus's **first documented compile-time-typed-
# reference-binding CLI pattern**.
